hrough hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid overwhipping. Transfer cream into bowl with reserved cooled pastry cream and fold through gently.","Place 2 tablespoons of the pastry cream onto each crêpe. Fold crêpe in half, then in half again to form triangles, and place onto a serving platter. Repeat with remaining pastry cream mixture and crêpes.","Pour reserved warm apricot sauce over crêpes. Top with remaining apricots (cut into small wedges) and mint leaves, then serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry cream","content":["30 g gluten free cornflour","60 g caster sugar","430 g full cream milk","4 egg yolks","30 g orange liqueur"]},{"title":"Apricot sauce","content":["30 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","125 g white sugar","410 g tinned apricots, drained","1 lemon, zested and juiced (approx. 40 g)","120 g orange juice","2 tsp gluten free cornflour","2 tsp water","30 g orange liqueur"]},{"title":"Coconut crêpes","content":["4 eggs","270 g coconut milk","30 g gluten free cornflour","40 g arrowroot flour","1 pinch salt","200 g pouring (whipping) cream","1 sprig fresh mint, leaves only, to serve"]}],"id":"r115277","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ER4r_GWJA-A\/XZWeFW5Zu_I\/AAAAAAAAeuk\/ZYkrEGGStWQ7vAH1xYwZvPPw-Jwb1aDAACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_SbTppHr_AjDotyXc.png","title":"Coconut crêpes with apricot sauce","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.23 g","fat":"21.76 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"46.95 g","calories":"1723 kJ \/ 410 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, bowl, small bowl , thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, jug, 1 plate, non-stick frying pan (15 cm), ladle, kitchen towel, serving platter, stove top","basicInfo":["easy","40m","2h","8 portions"]}